<article class="post-23894 post type-post status-publish format-standard has-post-thumbnail category-reading entry"><a href="http://www.ilona-andrews.com/black-parade-by-kyoko-m/" class="alignnone" aria-hidden="true"><img width="150" height="150" src="http://www.ilona-andrews.com/wp-content/plugins/jetpack/modules/lazy-images/images/1x1.trans.gif" class="entry-image attachment-post" alt="Black Parade by Kyoko M." itemprop="image" data-lazy-src="https://i1.wp.com/www.ilona-andrews.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/Black-parade.jpg?resize=150%2C150" data-lazy-srcset="https://i1.wp.com/www.ilona-andrews.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/Black-parade.jpg?resize=150%2C150 150w, https://i1.wp.com/www.ilona-andrews.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/Black-parade.jpg?zoom=2&amp;resize=150%2C150 300w, https://i1.wp.com/www.ilona-andrews.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/Black-parade.jpg?zoom=3&amp;resize=150%2C150 450w" data-lazy-sizes="(max-width: 150px) 100vw, 150px" /></a><header class="entry-header"><h2 class="entry-title" itemprop="headline"><a href="http://www.ilona-andrews.com/black-parade-by-kyoko-m/">Black Parade by Kyoko M.</a></h2></header><div class="entry-content"><p>The other day I was on Twitter, offering my opinion on the latest kerfluffle to the internet - because we all know how internet suffers without the benefit of my opinion ::eye roll: - and I ran into a &#x02026; <a href="http://www.ilona-andrews.com/black-parade-by-kyoko-m/" class="more-link">[Read More...]</a></p></div></article></div></section>
<section id="text-7" class="widget widget_text"><div class="widget-wrap"><h4 class="widget-title widgettitle">Welcome</h4>
			<div class="textwidget"><p><img class="alignleft size-full wp-image-235" style="margin: 0px 10px 3px 0px;" title="author1sm" src="http://www.ilona-andrews.com/wp-content/plugins/jetpack/modules/lazy-images/images/1x1.trans.gif" alt="author2sm" data-recalc-dims="1" data-lazy-src="https://i2.wp.com/ilona-andrews.com/images/author2sm.jpg"><noscript><img class="alignleft size-full wp-image-235" style="margin: 0px 10px 3px 0px;" title="author1sm" src="https://i2.wp.com/ilona-andrews.com/images/author2sm.jpg" alt="author2sm" data-recalc-dims="1" /></noscript>  "Ilona Andrews" is actually two people, Gordon and Ilona Andrews.  We write urban fantasy, an odd hybrid of a genre that includes elements of mystery, fantasy, and horror in a modern setting.   Right now we are working mainly on our  <a href="http://www.ilona-andrews.com/kate-daniels/">Kate Daniels</a> and our Hidden Legacy series.  We don't take ourselves too seriously.  </p>
<p>Please feel free to poke around.  There are free short stories under <a href="http://www.ilona-andrews.com/ebooks/">E Books</a> and some basic writing advice under <a href="http://www.ilona-andrews.com/category/writing-tricks/articles/">Articles</a>.  Also there is a free serial posted weekly.  It's called <a href="http://demo.ilona-andrews.com/">Innkeeper Chronicles</a> and we hope you'll check it out.</p>
</div>
